   "source": [
    "# GEX Analysis Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook introduces Gamma Exposure (GEX) analysis and demonstrates basic usage of the GEX Calculator.\n",
    "\n",
    "## What is GEX?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Gamma Exposure (GEX)** measures the aggregate gamma exposure of all option positions at a given price level.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Positive GEX**: Dealers are short gamma (they will hedge by selling into rallies and buying dips)\n",
    "- **Negative GEX**: Dealers are long gamma (they will hedge by buying rallies and selling dips)\n",
    "\n",
    "GEX is a key indicator of market microstructure and can help identify support/resistance levels."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '../')\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from src.core import GEXCalculator, OptionsChain\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style for plots\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid')\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Fetch Options Chain Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fetch options chain for QQQ (proxy for NQ/NDX)\n",
    "chain = OptionsChain(symbol='QQQ', data_source='yfinance')\n",
    "data = chain.fetch()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Retrieved {len(data)} options\")\n",
    "print(f\"Spot Price: ${chain.spot_price:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Expiration: {chain.expiration_date}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nData shape: {data.shape}\")\n",
    "print(data.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Clean and Prepare Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Clean the data\n",
    "clean_data = chain.clean_data()\n",
    "print(f\"After cleaning: {len(clean_data)} options\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get summary\n",
    "summary = chain.get_summary()\n",
    "print(\"\\nChain Summary:\")\n",
    "for key, value in summary.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {key}: {value}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get call-put breakdown\n",
    "cp_spread = chain.get_calls_puts_spread()\n",
    "print(f\"\\nCall/Put OI:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Total Call OI: {cp_spread['total_call_oi']:,.0f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Total Put OI: {cp_spread['total_put_oi']:,.0f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Put/Call Ratio: {cp_spread['put_call_ratio']:.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Calculate GEX"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize GEX calculator\n",
    "calculator = GEXCalculator(spot_price=chain.spot_price)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute GEX across price levels\n",
    "gex_results = calculator.compute_gex(clean_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Computed GEX for {len(gex_results)} price levels\")\n",
    "print(gex_results.head(10))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Identify Key Levels"
   ]
  },
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Find gamma flip points\n",
    "flip_points = calculator.find_gamma_flip_points(gex_results)\n",
    "print(f\"Found {len(flip_points)} gamma flip points:\")\n",
    "for i, fp in enumerate(flip_points[:5], 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"  {i}. Price ${fp['price']:.2f} - {fp['polarity'].upper()} GEX\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find support/resistance\n",
    "levels = calculator.find_support_resistance(gex_results)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nIdentified {len(levels['resistance'])} resistance levels and {len(levels['support'])} support levels\")\n",
    "print(f\"Resistance: {[f'{p:.2f}' for p in levels['resistance'][:3]]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Support: {[f'{p:.2f}' for p in levels['support'][:3]]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Visualize GEX"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot GEX\n",
    "colors = ['green' if x > 0 else 'red' for x in gex_results['gex']]\n",
    "ax.bar(gex_results['price'], gex_results['gex'], color=colors, alpha=0.6, width=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mark spot price\n",
    "ax.axvline(chain.spot_price, color='black', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'Spot: ${chain.spot_price:.2f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mark flip points\n",
    "for fp in flip_points:\n",
    "    ax.axvline(fp['price'], color='orange', linestyle=':', alpha=0.5, linewidth=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Price Level', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Gamma Exposure', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.set_title(f'GEX Profile for {chain.symbol} - {chain.expiration_date}', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Green bars = positive GEX (resistance)\")\n",
    "print(\"Red bars = negative GEX (support)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Positive GEX zones**: Dealers are short gamma. Markets tend to move away from these levels as dealers hedge.\n",
    "2. **Negative GEX zones**: Dealers are long gamma. Markets tend to stabilize around these levels.\n",
    "3. **Gamma flip points**: Transitions between dealer hedging behaviors. Can signal market inflection points.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Trading Implications:\n",
    "- Use GEX to complement technical analysis\n",
    "- Identify potential support/resistance levels\n",
    "- Understand dealer hedging impact on price action\n",
    "- Monitor gamma flips for potential breakouts"
   ]
  }
 ],
